## 3. System Overview

This document recorded the JUnit testing carried out on selected controller classes within the application. The testing focused on confirming that controller methods returned the correct view names, redirected users correctly where required, added model attributes only where expected, and raised the correct exceptions where invalid conditions were encountered. Mockito was used to mock dependent repositories, authentication, and model objects so that controller behaviour could be tested in isolation without relying on a live database or full application context. The testing also confirmed that the main student controller flow for home page access, revision access, test start and continuation, test submission, and results viewing behaved as expected.

