**Summary Notes:**  
JUnit testing confirmed that the selected controller classes behaved as expected in isolation. HomeController returned the correct home page view and handled the word of the day model attribute correctly. ResultsController returned the correct results view for the owning student, redirected unauthorised access attempts correctly, and raised the expected exceptions for missing test or user records. RevisionController returned the correct revision view, redirected users correctly where an active test already existed, mapped noun data correctly for the model, and raised the expected exception where the user could not be found. TestController correctly handled resume test behaviour, revision blocking behaviour, new test creation, continuation of existing tests, deletion of unsubmitted test data when starting a fresh test, test submission, redirect behaviour where tests had already been submitted, and the expected exceptions for missing user or test records.

